post_text:
Schenck High School Students may access their schedules on Tuesday, September 8th on the PowerSchool grade portal. Freshman and Sophomores may call or email to request changes to schedules on Tuesday and Wednesday (Sept 8 and 9), while Juniors and Seniors may call or email on Thursday and Friday ( Sept 10 and 11).

Please understand that, due to Covid 19 classroom spacing and size limitations, we have to restrict numbers in certain classes and not all electives may be available.

Thank you.

Mr. Eric Steeves
Superintendent/Guidance Director

Penquis Child Development has openings in our Pre-K classroom in East Millinocket!

This classroom is made possible by a wonderful long-running collaboration with East Millinocket Schools and Eastern Maine Community College.

We have openings for the fall for children who will turn 4 years-old by October 15th.Classroom sessions run 8a - 2p September to June.

More information can be found on our website: penquis.org or by emailing/calling Kelley Graffam at kgraffam@penquis.org / 207-973-3567

Opal Myrick staff would like to say thank you to everyone we saw during our parade this morning. It was great to see so many Opal kiddos, their families, and community members smiling and waving as we went by. 👋🏻😊

Thank you to everyone involved!! A huge thank you to the Penobscot County Sheriff Department along with East Millinocket and Medway Police, Fire, and EMTs! 🚓🚒🚑 We were so happy to have a school bus join us as well! 🚌

Even though this school year didn’t end with all of us all together at school, we were glad to be able to do something like this to see our students. We miss them more than words can say! 😊

We feel blessed to be part of and experience the joys of small town living. ❤️

post_text:
OPAL PARADE TIME!! 👋🏻

Please stop by the front school lawn tomorrow to get your pinwheel with your name on it between 10:00am and 2:00pm to wave during the parade.

We tried our best to create a route that would work well given the large area we need to cover. The route was driven through on Wednesday. At that time, there was construction in parts of Medway that we had to take into consideration for safety reasons. We were planning to go as far as Woodville, but due to the construction, we needed to plan differently.

The parade will start at 10:00am on Friday from the town garage in East. The route is in a picture below.

Please join us in a spot where our parade will pass by. We can’t wait to see all of your waving hands and smiling faces!! 😊💚

Please see the pictures below for more details about a student gift for K-4 Opal kiddos and the parade route.

post_text: All Summerfest 2020 events have been postponed until 2021 with the exception of fireworks. This year, in conjunction with Schenck High School, we will provide a fireworks show on the evening of graduation. The show will commence at 9:00 PM on June 6th. The fireworks will be shot off near the lower soccer field. We ask that the parking area behind Schenck High School be reserved for graduates and their immediate family members. If you attend the show, we ask that you follow social distancing guidelines. Congratulations class of 2020 and we hope to see you for Summerfest 2021!

post_text:
Greetings



The University of Maine System Admission departments hopes that you and your family are staying healthy during this challenging time with the pandemic that is affecting all of our lives. As schools and universities are shut down across the state we want to provide an opportunity for you and your current students to learn more about the public Universities in the great state of Maine.



We recognize that students may be facing unique challenges during the current pandemic including not being able to visit college campuses. The University of Maine System will be offering a Zoom session on Thursday, May 28th at 6:30pm to provide updates on new initiatives at our universities, the admissions process, and how we will be supporting students and their families as they work through the college selection process.



Please feel free to forward this invitation to any of your students. If you would like to register for the event please complete the registration form and we look forward to seeing you on May 28th.



The University of Maine System

post_text:
Greetings:

A committee has been formed consisting of myself, Dean of Students, John Montgomery, Senior Class Officers, Senior Representatives to our school board, Mrs. Lyons, Senior Class Advisor, Student Council/Yearbook Advisor, and the Chair of the East Millinocket School Board. This committee will be seeking guidance from state officials, medical experts and law enforcement in order to put together a solid plan for a proper Graduation Ceremony. We will be sharing our plan with seniors and their parents/guardians in the upcoming weeks. Once we have a tentative game plan, it will be posted on our website, Facebook page and will be sent to each graduating family. Thank you for your support and patience as we try to navigate these waters and I assure you that we will do the best we can to honor the accomplishments of this wonderful group of young people.

Justin Page
Principal

post_text: Due to the concerns of the nationwide pandemic, the East Millinocket Schools will be following the recommendations of the Maine Principals' Association, Maine CDC, Department of Education, the Governor's office, and other health agencies. As a result of their recommendations and/or directives, we will be postponing all spring sports, after school activities, school assemblies and our Winter Carnival until after April 27, 2020. During this time we will reassess how to make these opportunities available to our students so that they are able to take advantage of every educational and extracurricular function we traditionally offer. Thank you for your support and cooperation during this challenging situation.

post_text:
News

MPA Delays Start of Spring Sport Season

As you all know, implications from the Corona Virus have hit Maine. This being said, we have been in contact with the Maine CDC, DOE, Governor’s office, and other health agencies in regards to the best way to provide services that people need while keeping them safe.

On March 12, Governor Mills had a press conference stating that they are encouraging “Social Distancing.” By her definition, “social distancing” means groups of 250 or more people attending non-essential events should be delayed or postponed.

Because of this, the MPA Board of Directors and Interscholastic Management Committee voted today, March 13, 2020 to delay the start of the 2020 Spring sports pre-season practice until April 27, 2020. We will continue to monitor the situation and will make the appropriate changes as needed to ensure the safety of all students.

As you all know, implications from the Corona Virus have hit Maine. This being said, we have been in contact with the Maine CDC, DOE, Governor’s office, and other health agencies in regards to the best way to provide services that people need while keeping them safe.

Because of this, the MPA Board of Directors and Interscholastic Management Committee voted today, March 13, 2020 to delay the start of the 2020 Spring sports pre-season practice until April 27, 2020. We will continue to monitor the situation and will make the appropriate changes as needed to ensure the safety of all students.

George Hanley and Michelle Purcell recently came to 10th health class
to show the students what the heart saver program is about. Students
interested in certification cards will need to finish the 6 hour
course at the fire station in East Millinocket , March 3 and March 5
from 5-8pm. The course fee is 20 dollars for the certification cards.
Students who would like to take the course but do not have the money
will need to contact Mrs. Sprague. It will include Heartsaver, AED and
first aide certification.
The other pictures are of 10th grade Health class students
participating in class activities wearing simulation googles for under
the influence vision impairment.

post_text: Stearns will be hosting the MPA Regional Drama Festival this weekend, March 6th & 7th. Our very own Unified Performing Arts will be performing on Saturday, March 7th, at 6:00 p.m. The students will be presenting "Stress, Pressure, Doom and Other Teenage Delights" this is a family friendly play and all ages are encouraged to attend. Please check on the Millinocket Performing Arts Facebook page for other schools and times. Stearns will also be hosting a "Drama Night" on Tuesday, March 3rd, at 7:00 p.m. of the same performance. Admission will be by donation for the "Drama Night" only. Admission to the MPA Regional Drama Festival will be $10 for adults and $5 for students K-12.

post_text: Please be aware that the East Millinocket Schools have been very vigilant in making sure that all students are safe. We have been on a "soft" lock down, since being made aware of a threat directed toward our school. A "soft" lock down means that all outside doors are locked and all people entering and exiting the building have done so under staff supervision, ensuring that all visitors have been properly identified. We have also had the Chief of Police on campus since 9:00 a.m. this morning when we were first advised of the threat. We have also been in consultation with the Maine Department of Education to verify that our safety procedures are adequate to address this threat. Please also be advised that many schools throughout the state have be targeted in this threat, which pertains to the Impeachment hearings in Washington.
